{"id":"21-116","ticketId":"21","phase":"product","outcome":{"blocked":{}},"detail":"escalated — This needs clarification before it can proceed — it has open questions, ambiguity, or a potential conflict with the product\/vision. Please resolve the following (candidate options and a recommended default are given for each):\n\n**1. How should unanalyzed-language units appear in the report card?**\n   - Shown with a \"Limited Analysis\" badge and only git-history-based dimensions present, excluded from aggregate scores\n   - Completely omitted from the report card (only surfaced in the banner)\n   - Shown in the report card with all dimensions explicitly labeled \"Not Measured\" and grade N\/A\n   - _Recommended: Shown with a \"Limited Analysis\" badge and only git-history-based dimensions present, excluded from aggregate scores — aligns with the Vision's \"generic file-level fallback for any language\" while being honest about what was and wasn't measured_\n\n**2. Scope of the \"don't fabricate\" safety fix — apply to all ~15 unanalyzed languages (Ruby, Java, Kotlin, C\/C++, C#, PHP, Elixir, Scala, Lua, R, Zig, SQL, Protobuf, Shell) or Swift-only?**\n   - Apply to all unanalyzed languages in one pass — the scoring path is identical and systemic\n   - Swift-only now; other languages tracked as separate issues to be addressed when reported\n   - Swift plus any language explicitly listed in certifiableExts that also lacks an analyzer registration (defense-in-depth for the known set)\n   - _Recommended: Apply to all unanalyzed languages in one pass — the scoring bug is identical across all of them and fixing it per-language creates a whack-a-mole dynamic that undermines trust further_\n\n**3. Disposition of the dead SwiftLint policy rule in the init template?**\n   - Remove the dead rule now; add it back when the SwiftLint collector is implemented\n   - Leave the rule as forward-looking policy — it becomes active automatically when the collector lands\n   - Replace with a commented-out placeholder that documents the intended rule and required collector\n   - _Recommended: Remove the dead rule now — it is misleading to users who see it in their generated config and assume it is active. The rule can be reintroduced as part of the Swift tier work when the collector exists_\n\n**4. For dimensions where evidence is missing: absent from the score (per current doc comment) or explicitly surfaced as \"unknown\"?**\n   - Absent from the score entirely — they don't dilute the weighted average and the dimension count reflects only measured dimensions\n   - Present in the score as an explicit \"unknown\" sentinel (e.g., -1 or null in JSON) so consumers can distinguish \"not measured\" from \"measured poorly\"\n   - Absent from the numeric score but surfaced in the report card UI as \"Insufficient Data\" with the dimension name\n   - _Recommended: Absent from the numeric score entirely (per the existing doc comment contract) but surfaced in the report card UI as \"Insufficient Data\" — this gives honest visibility without diluting the average, and matches the principle of not penalizing what you can't measure_\n","at":805821654.494617}
